Campus Involvement: Daily Northwestern Business Office,  Spectrum Theatre Company, ShireiNU, Essence Tap Group, Gamma Phi Beta, ASB, Her Campus
Comments: I liked that she was able to tie her specific student group experience back to NU as a whole, and she was able to talk about creating her own student group without making it seem like NU is lacking in existing student group opportunities. However, her last answer about how NU students are passionate is good but does sound like every other tour guide application ever.
Majors: Theater, Sociology, IMC, Theater for Young Audiences Module

Campus Involvement: Camp Kesem, Delta Tau Delta, Intramural sports
Comments: His answers said essentially nothing about NU and too much about his own personal social life and self-discovery. But he seemed very enthusiastic, and it may be worth meeting him in an interview to get a sense of his personality.

Campus Involvement: Young Life, Wildside, Delta Sigma Pi
Comments: Really, really passionate about NU, but her stories about struggling with classwork and not being initially able to achieve a healthy work/life balance are too intense and would not be a good representation of NU. Too much personal detail (i.e., how she cried and sang the fight song when she got into NU)

Campus Involvement: Soul4Real A Capella,  Phi Mu Alpha, Northwestern University Tabletop Club, Communications Residential College IM Chair
Comments: Does a great job of speaking positively about NU's enabling students to pursue multiple things at once and answers have a "choose your own adventure" theme, which I liked.

Campus Involvement: Club Lacrosse Player, Women in Business Member, Institute for Student Business Education,  Book Buddies
Comments: You can tell they have lots of good ideas, but they have a hard time talking about just one thing at once.

Campus Involvement: Camp Kesem, Ahana Dance Project
Comments: Answers were pretty vague, and she spent most of her response to the re-branding NU slogan talking about how "AND is in our DNA" is a bad slogan.

Campus Involvement: Family Ambassador, Women in Law,  Chi Omega,  Donkey Show,  Northwestern Equestrian Team
Comments: Solid answers, connects her specific experiences to broader NU culture well

Campus Involvement: Sorority (unnamed), Northwestern News Network, the Blackout
Comments: This person is clearly extremely dedicated to being a tour guide (they clearly spent a long time on the application and has indicated that they have asked for advice from current tour guides), which I personally found a little overwhelming. But, I think if they are able to rein in their answers, they certainly have the necessary enthusiasm to be a great guide.

Campus Involvement: Asterik A Cappella, Norris employee, "one show per quarter(?)"
Comments: Really can't think of anything to say for this one. Some good answers, some not so good. Gave a "Why Northwestern" in video, which touched on students' passions which was nice.

Campus Involvement: ASG
Comments: I think this applicant could use another year before becoming a tour guide. In the re-branding question, they wrote that there are currently "no phrases that stand out to students" about NU, and I found it interesting (and maybe concerning) that they didn't think of "AND is in our DNA" or "Take a Northwestern Direction" or anything else.

Campus Involvement: SWE, Engineering World Health, Asian American Intervarsity, Delta Zeta, KASA
Comments: Honestly there were just some really irrelevant details shared here (i.e. "the ebb and flow of the lake inspires me")

Campus Involvement: The Blackout, Delta Gamma
Comments: Funny and original application, didn't talk too much about relevant NU information but took a risk by writing about Sargent.

Campus Involvement: Women in Leadership, Arch Scholars
Comments: Talks a lot about her personal experience with NU celebrating diversity and finding role models in faculty

Campus Involvement: Sigma Nu, KASA
Comments: Most answers were pretty general and could be applied to any college, and they talked more about their experience tour guiding at their previous boarding school than anything about NU

Comments: I thought their application was really well written, which makes me inclined to believe that they will be a good speaker.
